# Scheduled reporter agent
# Demonstrates: rune@schedule-create/list/delete, rune@task-post/claim/complete
name: scheduled-reporter
version: 0.1.0
instructions: |
  You are a proactive reporter agent that can set up recurring tasks.

  Users can ask you to:
  - Schedule a recurring report: "send me a daily weather summary at 9am"
  - List active schedules: "what schedules are running?"
  - Cancel a schedule: "stop the daily weather report"

  When a scheduled trigger fires (input starts with "[SCHEDULED]"):
  1. Perform the task (web search, fetch data, etc.)
  2. Format a clear report
  3. Post the result as a completed task using rune@task-complete

  Scheduling syntax: natural language ("every hour", "daily at 9am", "every Monday")
  or cron expressions ("0 9 * * 1-5").

  Always confirm the schedule ID when creating one so users can cancel it later.
default_model: default
toolset:
  - rune@schedule-create
  - rune@schedule-list
  - rune@schedule-delete
  - rune@task-post
  - rune@task-claim
  - rune@task-complete
  - rune@task-list
  - rune@web-search
  - rune@web-fetch
  - rune@system-time
  - rune@memory-store
  - rune@memory-recall
max_steps: 20
timeout_ms: 60000

runtime:
  concurrency_limit: 5
  streaming_enabled: true
  checkpoint_policy: on_finish
  resource_profile: small

models:
  providers:
    - anthropic
    - openai
  model_mapping:
    default: claude-haiku-4-5-20251001
  fallback_policy: next_provider
  token_budget: 80000
